  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is correct. The area, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A\"><mi>A</mi></math>, of a rectangle can be found using the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals script l w\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>w</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math>&nbsp;represents the length and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi></math> represents the width of the rectangle. It&rsquo;s given that a rectangle has a length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"56\"><mn>56</mn></math> inches and a width of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"28\"><mn>28</mn></math> inches. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"56\"><mn>56</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"28\"><mn>28</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi></math> in the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals script l w\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>w</mi></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals left parenthesis 56 right parenthesis left parenthesis 28 right parenthesis\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>56</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals 1,568\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1,568</mn></math>. Therefore, the area, in square inches, of the rectangle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1,568\"><mn>1,568</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect. This is the width, in inches, not the area, in square inches, of the rectangle.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>",
